# Tenant identifier denylist

The strings below are banned anywhere in this repository (source, tests,
fixtures, comments, CHANGELOG, release notes, commit messages). The
`Tenant-name denylist` CI job in `.github/workflows/ci.yml` greps the
working tree on every push / PR and fails the build if any match is found.

The CI patterns are obfuscated via character classes / UTF-8 hex so this
documentation file itself doesn't trip the scan.

If you need a placeholder for documentation or fixtures, use one of:

- `ACME` (default contract-number prefix)
- `Acme Procurement Co.` / `AcmeProcure` (default company name / short name)
- Chinese placeholder: 示例公司
- `TENANT-...` (when illustrating that tenants supply their own value)

## Banned categories (described, not literal)

- The 4-letter ASCII prefix used by an early tenant before
  `contract.number_prefix` was made configurable. Lowercase variant also banned.
- The 2-character Chinese name fragment (Unicode points U+4F73 U+671F).
- The internal-domain hostname suffix `jqdomain`.

## Policy

Any production-tenant-specific identifier that lands in code MUST be
configurable via `system_parameters` (see `contract.number_prefix` for
the canonical pattern), never hard-coded.
